src/tests/bundles/bionic-rocky.yaml.message:
@Peter - that's a good point. A subsequent patch should be proposed to the cinder charm to deprecate the lvm specific options there, pointing users to the cinder-lvm charm.

@Luciano - the point was that it might be taking the block device you expected for the cinder-lvm charm configuration. i.e. if the cinder charm has block-device configured to /dev/vdb then that may be taking the block device you'd want to use for the cinder-lvm charm.

We'll need an upgrade note to tell users that are using the LVM storage with the cinder charm to deploy cinder-lvm with the same volume group name/configurations and to unset the options in the cinder charm.

